{"title_page": "Panasonic Lumix DC-GH5", "text_new": "{{Infobox camera\n| camera_name      = [[Panasonic]] [[Lumix]] DC-GH5\n| image            = [[File:Panasonic.Lumix.DC-GH5.jpg|300px]]\n| type             = [[Micro Four Thirds system]] mirrorless camera\n| lens_mount       = [[Micro Four Thirds system]] mount\n| sensor           = 4/3-type\n| sensor_type      = [[CMOS]]\n| sensor_size      = 17.3 x 13 mm (4:3 aspect ratio)\n| sensor_maker     = [[Sony]]<ref>https://chipworks1.force.com/DefaultStore/ccrz__ProductDetails?viewState=DetailView&cartID=&sku=DEF-1705-804</ref>\n| res              = 5184 x 3888 px (20.1 [[megapixels]])\n| speedRange       = ISO 200-25600, extendable to 100\n| recording_medium = 2x [[Secure Digital|SD]] / [[Secure Digital#SDHC|SDHC]] / [[Secure Digital#SDXC|SDXC]]\n| focus_type       = Switchable Auto and Manual\n| fmode            = AF-C (Continuous-Servo), AF-F (Flexible AF), AF-S (Single Servo AF), Manual Focus\n| farea            = 255 [[Autofocus#Contrast Detection|Contrast Detection AF]]\n| emode            = Program AE; [[Aperture Priority]], [[Shutter priority]], Manual\n| mmode            = Center-weighted, Multiple, Spot\n| fsynch           = 1/250\n| flbkt            = \u00b13 EV in \u2153 EV steps\n| shutter          = [[Focal-plane shutter]] / Electronic shutter\n| shutterRange     = 1/16000s - 60s, BULB\n| cont             = 12 fps at 20.3 MP <br/> 30 fps at 18MP <br/> 60 fps at 8 MP\n| viewfinder       = [[OLED]] viewfinder; 3.6M dots\n| magnification    = 0.76x\n| WB               = Auto, Cloudy, Shade, Incadescent, Flash, Daylight, White Set 1/2/3/4, Custom WB based on color temperature\n| vidrecord        = [[AVCHD]] / MP4 / MOV <br/> 4096 x 2160 (24p, 25p) <br/> 3840 x 2160 (24p, 25p, 30p, 50p, 60p) <br/> 3328 x 2496p (24p, 25p, 30p 50p, 60p) <br/> 1920 x 1080p (24p, 25p, 30p, 50p, 60p)\n| rearLCD          = 3.2\", 1.6M Dots, free-angle\n| battery          = 7.2v 1860 mAh Lithium-ion battery pack\n| interface_AVout  = <!-- Type of video and/or audio output port(s) available (e.g. HDMI, USB, IEEE 1394) -->\n| interface_Data   = [[Wi-Fi]], [[Bluetooth]], full-sized [[HDMI]] Type-A, [[USB#USB 3.1|USB 3.1]] Gen1 5Gbit/s,\n| dimensions       = 138.5 x 98.1 x 87.4 mm (5.5 x 3.9 x 3.4\")\n| weight           = 725 g (1.595 lb) (battery and SD cards inserted)\n| predecessor      = [[Panasonic Lumix DMC-GH4|Lumix GH4]]\n| date             = March 2017\n| madeIn           = {{CHN}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Panasonic Lumix DC-GH5''' is a [[Micro Four Thirds]] mirrorless interchangeable lens camera body announced by [[Panasonic]] on 4 January 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dpreview.com/products/panasonic/slrs/panasonic_dcgh5|title=Panasonic Lumix DC-GH5: Digital Photography Review|author=|date=|website=www.dpreview.com|accessdate=18 April 2018}}</ref>\n\nIt is the first mirrorless camera capable of shooting [[4K resolution]] video with [[Color depth#Deep Color (30/36/48-bit)|10-bit color]] with [[Chroma subsampling#4:2:2|4:2:2 chroma subsampling]], along with recording in 4K 60p or 50p (but only in 8 bit). It also captures both 4K and [[1080p|Full HD]] without time limits.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.digitaltrends.com/photography/panasonic-gh5-gx480-fz80-cameras-ces-2017/ |title=Panasonic GH5 shoots 4K at 60 frames per second \u2014 with no time limits |author=Hillary Grigonis |date=January 4, 2017}}</ref> On September 28, 2017, Panasonic released firmware update 2.0 which added support for [[Hybrid Log-Gamma]] (HLG) recording, along with a higher 400Mbit/s bit rate All-i recording mode.<ref name=PanasonicFirmwareGH5September2017>{{cite news |title=Panasonic Releases GH5 Firmware 2.0 with Anamorphic and More |author=Daron James |publisher=No Film School |url=https://nofilmschool.com/2017/09/panasonic-gh5-adds-anamorphic-and-more-firmware-update |date=2017-09-28 |accessdate=2017-12-09}}</ref> The camera features 5-axis in-body stabilization, and, according to Panasonic, is freeze-proof, dust-proof, and splash-proof. <ref name=ThePanasonicGH5isabigbadmirrorlesscamerathat'sallaboutvideo\n>{{cite news |title=The Panasonic GH5 is a big, bad mirrorless camera that's all about video\n |author=Sean O'Kane |publisher=The Verge |url=https://www.theverge.com/2017/1/4/14145730/panasonic-gh5-fz80-gx850-compact-cameras-ces-2017 |date=2017-01-04 |accessdate=2019-10-23}}</ref>\n\nThe later-released sister model [[Panasonic Lumix DC-GH5S]] is a more specialized filmmakers' camera that adds greater low-light sensitivity, a multi-aspect image sensor, and expanded DCI 4K options. It has 10 Megapixels, and is equipped without a stabilised image sensor.<ref name=PanasonicGH5sAnnouncement>{{cite news |title=Say Hello to the New, Even More Filmmaker-Focused GH5S |author=Jon Fusco |publisher=No Film School |url=https://nofilmschool.com/2018/01/say-hello-new-even-more-filmmaker-focused-gh5s |date=2018-01-08 |accessdate=2018-02-06}}</ref>\nThe Panasonic GH5S is an even more video-centric variant of the GH5: it can shoot either DCI or UHD 4K footage natively (i.e. where one capture pixel = one output pixel) at up to 60p. As well as the ability to shoot DCI 4K at higher frame rates, Panasonic claim the GH5S's larger pixels and 'Dual Native ISO' sensor will shoot significantly better footage in low light.\n\n== Gallery ==\n<gallery caption=\"Panasonic Lumix DC-GH5>\nFile:Panasonic.Lumix.DC-GH5.back.jpg|Back view with out-swivelled monitor\nFile:Panasonic.Lumix.DC-GH5.Leica.12-60.front view.jpg|Front view with zoom lens Leica DG Vario-Elmarit 12\u201360&nbsp;mm f/2.8\u20134.0\nFile:Panasonic.Lumix.DC-GH5.Leica.12-60.perspective view.jpg|Perspective view with zoom lens Leica DG Vario-Elmarit 12\u201360&nbsp;mm f/2.8\u20134.0\n</gallery>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commonscat|Panasonic Lumix DC-GH5}}\n*{{official|panasonic.jp/dc/g_series/gh5/}}\n\n{{Micro Four Thirds cameras}}\n{{DSLR cameras with movie mode}}\n{{camera-stub}}\n\n[[Category:Panasonic mirrorless interchangeable lens cameras|GH5]]\n[[Category:Cameras introduced in 2017]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox camera\n| camera_name      = [[Panasonic]] [[Lumix]] DC-GH5\n| image            = [[File:Panasonic.Lumix.DC-GH5.jpg|300px]]\n| type             = [[Micro Four Thirds system]] mirrorless camera\n| lens_mount       = [[Micro Four Thirds system]] mount\n| sensor           = 4/3-type\n| sensor_type      = [[CMOS]]\n| sensor_size      = 17.3 x 13 mm (4:3 aspect ratio)\n| sensor_maker     = [[Sony]]<ref>https://chipworks1.force.com/DefaultStore/ccrz__ProductDetails?viewState=DetailView&cartID=&sku=DEF-1705-804</ref>\n| res              = 5184 x 3888 px (20.1 [[megapixels]])\n| speedRange       = ISO 200-25600, extendable to 100\n| recording_medium = 2x [[Secure Digital|SD]] / [[Secure Digital#SDHC|SDHC]] / [[Secure Digital#SDXC|SDXC]]\n| focus_type       = Switchable Auto and Manual\n| fmode            = AF-C (Continuous-Servo), AF-F (Flexible AF), AF-S (Single Servo AF), Manual Focus\n| farea            = 255 [[Autofocus#Contrast Detection|Contrast Detection AF]]\n| emode            = Program AE; [[Aperture Priority]], [[Shutter priority]], Manual\n| mmode            = Center-weighted, Multiple, Spot\n| fsynch           = 1/250\n| flbkt            = \u00b13 EV in \u2153 EV steps\n| shutter          = [[Focal-plane shutter]] / Electronic shutter\n| shutterRange     = 1/16000s - 60s, BULB\n| cont             = 12 fps at 20.3 MP <br /> 30 fps at 18MP <br /> 60 fps at 8 MP\n| viewfinder       = [[OLED]] viewfinder; 3.6M dots\n| magnification    = 0.76x\n| WB               = Auto, Cloudy, Shade, Incadescent, Flash, Daylight, White Set 1/2/3/4, Custom WB based on color temperature\n| vidrecord        = [[AVCHD]] / MP4 / MOV <br /> 4096 x 2160 (24p, 25p) <br /> 3840 x 2160 (24p, 25p, 30p, 50p, 60p) <br /> 3328 x 2496p (24p, 25p, 30p 50p, 60p) <br /> 1920 x 1080p (24p, 25p, 30p, 50p, 60p)\n| rearLCD          = 3.2\", 1.6M Dots, free-angle \n| battery          = 7.2v 1860 mAh Lithium-ion battery pack\n| interface_AVout  = <!-- Type of video and/or audio output port(s) available (e.g. HDMI, USB, IEEE 1394) -->\n| interface_Data   = [[Wi-Fi]], [[Bluetooth]], full-sized [[HDMI]] Type-A, [[USB#USB 3.1|USB 3.1]] Gen1 5Gbit/s, \n| dimensions       = 138.5 x 98.1 x 87.4 mm (5.5 x 3.9 x 3.4\") \n| weight           = 725 g (1.595 lb) (battery and SD cards inserted)\n| predecessor      = [[Panasonic Lumix DMC-GH4|Lumix GH4]]\n| date             = March 2017\n| madeIn           = {{CHN}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Panasonic Lumix DC-GH5''' is a [[Micro Four Thirds]] mirrorless interchangeable lens camera body announced by [[Panasonic]] on 4 January 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dpreview.com/products/panasonic/slrs/panasonic_dcgh5|title=Panasonic Lumix DC-GH5: Digital Photography Review|author=|date=|website=www.dpreview.com|accessdate=18 April 2018}}</ref>\n\nIt is the first mirrorless camera capable of shooting [[4K resolution]] video with [[Color depth#Deep Color (30/36/48-bit)|10-bit color]] with [[Chroma subsampling#4:2:2|4:2:2 chroma subsampling]], along with recording in 4K 60p or 50p (but only in 8 bit). It also captures both 4K and [[1080p|Full HD]] without time limits.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.digitaltrends.com/photography/panasonic-gh5-gx480-fz80-cameras-ces-2017/ |title=Panasonic GH5 shoots 4K at 60 frames per second \u2014 with no time limits |author=Hillary Grigonis |date=January 4, 2017}}</ref> On September 28, 2017, Panasonic released firmware update 2.0 which added support for [[Hybrid Log-Gamma]] (HLG) recording, along with a higher 400Mbit/s bit rate All-i recording mode.<ref name=PanasonicFirmwareGH5September2017>{{cite news |title=Panasonic Releases GH5 Firmware 2.0 with Anamorphic and More |author=Daron James |publisher=No Film School |url=https://nofilmschool.com/2017/09/panasonic-gh5-adds-anamorphic-and-more-firmware-update |date=2017-09-28 |accessdate=2017-12-09}}</ref> The camera features 5-axis in-body stabilization, and, according to Panasonic, is freeze-proof, dust-proof, and splash-proof. <ref name=ThePanasonicGH5isabigbadmirrorlesscamerathat'sallaboutvideo\n>{{cite news |title=The Panasonic GH5 is a big, bad mirrorless camera that's all about video\n |author=Sean O'Kane |publisher=The Verge |url=https://www.theverge.com/2017/1/4/14145730/panasonic-gh5-fz80-gx850-compact-cameras-ces-2017 |date=2017-01-04 |accessdate=2019-10-23}}</ref>\n\nThe later-released sister model [[Panasonic Lumix DC-GH5S]] is a more specialized filmmakers' camera that adds greater low-light sensitivity, a multi-aspect image sensor, and expanded DCI 4K options. It has 10 Megapixels, and is equipped without a stabilised image sensor.<ref name=PanasonicGH5sAnnouncement>{{cite news |title=Say Hello to the New, Even More Filmmaker-Focused GH5S |author=Jon Fusco |publisher=No Film School |url=https://nofilmschool.com/2018/01/say-hello-new-even-more-filmmaker-focused-gh5s |date=2018-01-08 |accessdate=2018-02-06}}</ref>\nThe Panasonic GH5S is an even more video-centric variant of the GH5: it can shoot either DCI or UHD 4K footage natively (i.e. where one capture pixel = one output pixel) at up to 60p. As well as the ability to shoot DCI 4K at higher frame rates, Panasonic claim the GH5S's larger pixels and 'Dual Native ISO' sensor will shoot significantly better footage in low light.\n\n== Gallery ==\n<gallery caption=\"Panasonic Lumix DC-GH5>\nFile:Panasonic.Lumix.DC-GH5.back.jpg|Back view with out-swivelled monitor\nFile:Panasonic.Lumix.DC-GH5.Leica.12-60.front view.jpg|Front view with zoom lens Leica DG Vario-Elmarit 12\u201360&nbsp;mm f/2.8\u20134.0\nFile:Panasonic.Lumix.DC-GH5.Leica.12-60.perspective view.jpg|Perspective view with zoom lens Leica DG Vario-Elmarit 12\u201360&nbsp;mm f/2.8\u20134.0\n</gallery>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commonscat|Panasonic Lumix DC-GH5}}\n*{{official|panasonic.jp/dc/g_series/gh5/}}\n\n{{Micro Four Thirds cameras}}\n{{DSLR cameras with movie mode}